The paper deals with the nearest neighbor problem, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of spherical codes and lattices, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The analysis of collision probabilities and query exponents also involves concepts from machine learning (cs.LG) and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
